Now can't you see we're [C]on our way
We're [D7]going [G7]home once [C]more
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
It will be grand to see our neighbors
That we knew way back [G7]when
And to have an old time party
How I long for them [C]again
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
Choo choo train just keep on rocking
Come on and [C7]let the black smoke [F]roll
Now can't you see we're [C]on our way
We're [D7]going [G7]home once [C]more
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
Yes we're going home for Christmas
It's been such a long long [G7]time
Since we've all been together
Where the family use to [C]dine
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 8}
They will come from all directions
From the [C7]hills and from the [F]shore
This is the day we're [C]on our way
We're [D7]going [G7]home once [C]more
{end_of_verse}
